    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Scopolina tangutica are fever, where its antipyretic properties reduce body temperature, and inflammatory conditions, such as arthritis, which are alleviated by its anti-inflammatory activity. Its antispasmodic properties also make it effective in treating epilepsy, a neurological disorder characterized by recurrent seizures. Furthermore, Scopolina tangutica has been shown to exhibit antimicrobial activity, which can aid in the treatment of bacterial infections like tuberculosis. Additionally, its antitumor properties make it a potential treatment for cancer, specifically leukemia, by inhibiting cell proliferation. These properties also contribute to its use in treating gastrointestinal disorders, such as irritable bowel syndrome.",
