    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Scopolina tangutica are its antimicrobial activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and other secondary metabolites. The plant also exhibits anti-inflammatory properties, likely due to the presence of sesquiterpenes and phenolic compounds, making it a potential treatment for various inflammatory conditions. Additionally, Scopolina tangutica has been found to possess antioxidant properties, which can be attributed to the presence of saponins and other bioactive compounds, helping to protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. Its antiviral activity may also be attributed to the presence of volatile oils and other bioactive compounds, making it a potential treatment for various viral infections. The plant's immunomodulatory properties, which can be attributed to the presence of alkaloids and other bioactive compounds, may also be beneficial in modulating the immune system and preventing diseases.",
