    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Scopolina tangutica are alkaloids including Scopolin A and B, which are shown to have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. Scopolin A has been found to possess neuroprotective effects by inhibiting acetylcholinesterase, an enzyme involved in the progression of Alzheimer's disease. Additionally, the plant contains flavonoids such as quercetin and kaempferol, which have been proven to exhibit antitumor and antimicrobial activities. The presence of phenolic acids like caffeic and ferulic acid contributes to its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, while the triterpenoids and sterols present in Scopolina tangutica have been found to possess immunomodulatory effects. These diverse healing constituents suggest that Scopolina tangutica may have potential applications in treating neurodegenerative diseases, cancer, and infections.",
