    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Scopolina tangutica are tincture, infusion, decoction, tea infusion, and salve. Tincture is a concentrated liquid solution prepared by steeping the root and rhizome of Scopolina tangutica in a solvent such as ethanol, commonly used to treat anxiety and insomnia. Infusion involves steeping the dried root and rhizome in hot water to produce a tea-like liquid, used to treat conditions like fever and inflammation. Decoction is a method of extraction using boiling water to release the active compounds from the root and rhizome, often used to treat gastrointestinal issues. Salve is a topical application prepared by infusing the root and rhizome in a carrier oil, used to treat skin conditions and wounds.",
