    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Scopolina tangutica improperly include experiencing hallucinations, which can be attributed to its anticholinergic properties that disrupt the normal functioning of the brain's neurotransmitters, leading to altered perception and cognition. Additionally, individuals may develop delirium, a state of confusion and altered consciousness, due to the drug's ability to impair cognitive function and judgment. Furthermore, Scopolina tangutica can cause tachycardia, a rapid heart rate, as a result of its sympathomimetic effects, which stimulate the heart and nervous system. In severe cases, improper use of the drug can lead to seizures, a risk that is exacerbated by the drug's ability to disrupt the balance of electrolytes in the body. These side effects can occur due to the drug's interaction with the central nervous system and its ability to affect the brain's neurotransmitters, heart rate, and other physiological processes.",
    "uses": "Scopolina tangutica is known for its potential medicinal uses, particularly in traditional Chinese medicine. It is believed to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, which may help alleviate symptoms of various health conditions. The plant's extracts have been studied for their potential to treat conditions such as fever, rheumatism, and skin problems. However, more research is needed to fully understand its effects and potential applications. Some studies suggest that Scopolina tangutica may also have antimicrobial and antiviral properties.",
    "taxonomy": "Scopolina tangutica belongs to the family Solanaceae and is classified as a type of plant in the genus Scopolina. It is a species of flowering plant that is native to China. The plant is further classified as a type of perennial that grows in the mountainous regions. The classification of Scopolina tangutica is based on its morphological characteristics and molecular phylogenetic studies. It is closely related to other plants in the same family, such as Datura and Brugmansia.",
    "benefits": "Scopolina tangutica is a plant known for its medicinal properties, particularly in traditional Chinese medicine. It has been used to treat various ailments, including fever, rheumatism, and skin conditions. Scopolina tangutica is also believed to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant effects, which may help to reduce stress and improve overall health. However, more research is needed to fully understand its health benefits and potential side effects. Some studies suggest that Scopolina tangutica may have antimicrobial properties, which could be beneficial in preventing infections.",
    "parts": "Scopolina tangutica is a plant species known for its medicinal properties, and its medicinal parts are primarily the roots and rhizomes, which contain alkaloids such as scopolamine and hyoscyamine. These compounds have been used in traditional medicine to treat various conditions, including pain, inflammation, and digestive issues. The roots and rhizomes are typically harvested in the fall, dried, and then processed for use in herbal remedies. The medicinal parts of Scopolina tangutica are rich in bioactive compounds that have been shown to have potential anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial effects. Further research is needed to fully understand the therapeutic potential of this plant.",
    "intro": "Scopolina tangutica, also known as Tangut Scopolia, is a plant species native to the mountainous regions of China, belonging to the Solanaceae family. The plant has been used in traditional Chinese medicine to treat various ailments, including fever, rheumatism, and respiratory issues, thanks to its anti-inflammatory, antiviral, and antipyretic properties. The bioactive constituents of Scopolina tangutica include scopolin, a scopoletin glycoside, along with other alkaloids and flavonoids, which are responsible for its medicinal effects. Traditionally, the plant is prepared into herbal teas, capsules, or tinctures, and is also used in combination with other herbs to create formulas for treating conditions such as bronchitis and pneumonia."
